obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (29900)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29900&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Hindu Minority and Guardianship Act,`
  line 1956.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1*** and applies also to Hindus domiciled in the territories to`
  line `which this Act extends who are outside the said territories.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (29901)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Act to be supplemental to Act 8 of 1890.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29901&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and`
  line `not, save as hereinafter expressly provided, in derogation of, the Guardians and Wards Act, 1890`
  line `(8 of 1890).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (29902)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Application of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3(1) and the Schedule (w.e.f. 24-5-1968).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29902&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act applies,--`
  line
  line `(a) to any person who is a Hindu by religion in any of its forms or developments, including a`
  line `Virashaiva, a Lingayat or a follower of the Brahmo, Prarthana or AryaSamaj;`
  line
  line `(b) to any person who is a Buddhist, Jain or Sikh by religion, and`
  line
  line `(c) to any other person domiciled in the territories to which this Act extends who is not a Muslim,`
  line `Christian, Parsi or Jew by religion unless it is proved that any such person would not have been`
  line `governed by the Hindu law or by any custom or usage as part of that law in respect of any of the`
  line `matters dealt with herein if this Act had not been passed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The following persons are Hindus, Buddhists, Jains, or Sikhs by religion, as the case`
  line `may be:--`
  line
  line `(i) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, both of whose parents are Hindus, Buddhists, Jains or`
  line `Sikhs by religion;`
  line
  line `(ii) any child, legitimate or illegitimate, one of whose parents is a Hindu, Buddhist, Jain or`
  line `Sikh by religion and who is brought up as a member of the tribe, community, group or family to`
  line `which such parent belongs or belonged; and`
  line
  line `(iii) any person who is convert or re-convert to the Hindu, Buddhist, Jain or Sikh religion.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) nothing contained in this Act shall apply to`
  line `the members of any scheduled Tribe within the meaning of clause (25) of article 366 of the Constitution`
  line `unless the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, otherwise directs.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), nothing contained in this Act shall`
  line `apply to the Renoncants of the Union Territory of Pondicherry.]`
  line
  line `(3) The expression "Hindu", in any provision of this Act shall be construed as if it included a person`
  line `who, though not a Hindu by religion, is, nevertheless, a person to whom this Act applies by virtue of the`
  line `provisions contained in this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (29903)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29903&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `In this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) "minor" means a person who has not completed the age of eighteen years;`
  line
  line `(b) "guardian" means a person having the care of the person of a minor or of his property or of`
  line `both his person andproperty, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a natural guardian,`
  line
  line `(ii) a guardian appointed by the will of the minors father or mother,`
  line
  line `(iii) a guardian appointed or declared by a court, and`
  line
  line `(iv) a person empowered to act as such by or under any enactment relating to any Court of`
  line wards.
  line
  line `(c) "natural guardian" means any of the guardians mentioned in section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (29904)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Over-riding effect of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29904&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) any text, rule or interpretation of Hindu Law or any custom or usage as part of that law in`
  line `force immediately before the commencement of this Act Shall cease to have effect with respect to any`
  line `matter for which provision is made in this Act.`
  line
  line `(b) any other law in force immediately before the commencement of this Act shall cease to have`
  line `effect in so far as it is inconsistent with any of the provisions contained in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (29905)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Natural guardians of a Hindu minor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29905&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The natural guardians of a Hindu minor; in respect of the`
  line `minor's person as well as in respect of the minor's property (excluding his or her undivided interest in`
  line `joint family property), are--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a boy or an unmarried girl--the father, and after him, the mother: provided that`
  line `the custody of a minor who has not completed the age of five years shall ordinarily be with the`
  line mother;
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an illegitimate boy or an illegitimate unmarried girl--the mother, and after her,`
  line `the father;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a married girl the husband:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be entitled to act as the natural guardian of a minor under the provisions`
  line `of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) if he has ceased to be a Hindu, or`
  line
  line `(b) if he has completely and finally renounced the world by becoming a hermit (vanaprastha) or`
  line `an ascetic (yati or sanyasi).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, the expressions "father" and "mother" do not include a step-father and`
  line `a step-mother.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (29906)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Natural guardianship of adopted son.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29906&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The natural guardianship of an adopted son who is a`
  line `minor passes, on adoption, to the adoptive father and after him to the adoptive mother.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (29907)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Powers of natural guardian.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29907&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The natural guardian of a Hindu minor has power, subject to`
  line `the provisions of this section, to do all acts which are necessary or reasonable and proper for the benefit of`
  line `the minor or for the realization, protection or benefit of the minor's estate; but the guardian can in no case`
  line `bind the minor by a personal covenant.`
  line
  line `(2) The natural guardian shall not, without the previous permission of the court,--`
  line
  line `(a) mortgage or charge, or transfer by sale, gift, exchange or otherwise, any part of the`
  line `immovable property of the minor; or`
  line
  line `(b) lease any part of such property for a term exceeding five years or for a term extending more`
  line `than one year beyond the date on which the minor will attain majority.`
  line
  line `(3) Any disposal of immovable property by a natural guardian, in contravention of sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2), is voidable at the instance of the minor or any person claiming under him.`
  line
  line `(4) No court shall grant permission to the natural guardian to do any of the acts mentioned in subsection`
  line `(2) except in case of necessity or for an evident advantage to the minor.`
  line
  line `(5) The Guardians and Wards Act, 1890 (8 of 1890), shall apply to and in respect of an application for`
  line `obtaining the permission of the court under sub-section (2) in all respects as if it were an application for`
  line `obtaining the permission of the court under section 29 of that Act, and in particular--`
  line
  line `(a) proceedings in connection with the application shall be deemed to be proceedings under that`
  line `Act within the meaning of section 4A thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) the court shall observe the procedure and have the powers specified in sub-sections (2), (3)`
  line `and (4) of section 31 of that Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) an appeal shall lie from an order of the court refusing permission to the natural guardian to do`
  line `any of the Acts mentioned in sub-section (2) of this section to the court to which appeals ordinarily lie`
  line `from the decisions of that court.`
  line
  line `(6) In this section, "Court" means the city civil court or a district court or a court empowered under`
  line `section 4A of the Guardians and Wards Act, 1890 (8 of 1890), within the local limits of whose`
  line `jurisdiction the immovable property in respect of which the application is made is situate, and where the`
  line `immovable property is situate within the jurisdiction of more than one such court, means the court within`
  line `the local limits of whose jurisdiction any portion of the property is situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (29908)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Testamentary guardians and their powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29908&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Hindu father entitled to act as the natural`
  line `guardian of his minor legitimate children may, by will appoint a guardian for any of them in respect of the`
  line `minor's person or in respect of the minor's property (other than the undivided interest referred to in`
  line `section 12) or in respect of both.`
  line
  line `(2) An appointment made under sub-section (1) shall have no effect if the father predeceases the`
  line `mother, but shall revive if the mother dies without appointing, by will, any person as guardian.`
  line
  line `(3) A Hindu widow entitled to act as the natural guardian of her minor legitimate children, and a`
  line `Hindu mother entitled to act as the natural guardian of her minor legitimate children by reason of the fact`
  line `that the father has become disentitled to act as such, may, by will, appoint a guardian for any of them in`
  line `respect of the minor's person or in respect of the minor's property (other than the undivided interest`
  line `referred to in section 12) or in respect of both.`
  line
  line `(4) A Hindu mother entitled to act as the natural guardian of her minor illegitimate children may; by`
  line `will, appoint a guardian for any of them in respect of the minor's person or in respect of the minor's`
  line `property or in respect of both.`
  line
  line `(5) The guardian so appointed by will has the right to act as the minor's guardian after the death of`
  line `the minor's father or mother, as the case may be, and to exercise all the rights of a natural guardian under`
  line `this Act to such extent and subject to such restrictions, if any, as are specified in this Act and in the will.`
  line
  line `(6) The right of the guardian so appointed by will shall, where the minor is a girl, cease on her`
  line marriage.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (29909)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Incapacity of minor to act as guardian of property.`
  content `A minor shall be incompetent to act as guardian of the property of any minor.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29909&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (29910)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `De facto guardian not to deal with minor’s property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29910&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `After the commencement of this Act,`
  line `no person shall be entitled to dispose of, or deal with, the property of a Hindu minor merely on the ground`
  line `of his or her being the de facto guardian of the minor.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (29911)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Guardian not to be appointed for minors undivided interest in joint family property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29911&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where a minor has an undivided interest in joint family property and the property is under the`
  line `management of an adult member of the family, no guardian shall be appointed for the minor in respect of`
  line `such undivided interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to affect the jurisdiction of a High Court to`
  line `appoint a guardian in respect of such interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (29912)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Welfare of minor to be paramount consideration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902&sectionId=29912&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00013_195632_1517807320902
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) In the appointment of declaration of`
  line `any person as guardian of a Hindu minor by a court, the welfare of the minor shall be the paramount`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be entitled to the guardianship by virtue of the provisions of this Act or of any law`
  line `relating to guardianship in marriage among Hindus, if the court is of opinion that his or her guardianship`
  line `will not be for the welfare of the minor.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
